==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pentacrostic
<hw>Pen`ta*cros"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Penta-</ets> + <ets>acrostic</ets>.]</ety> <def>A set of
verses so disposed that the name forming the subject of the acrostic
occurs five times -- the whole set of verses being divided into five
different parts from top to bottom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentad</ent>⟦br⟧
